[65.170466, "o", "8;2;30;41;59m                                                                                                                                                                                        \u001b[0m\r\n  \u001b[1;38;2;245;158;11mASST\u001b[0m  \u001b[38;2;107;113;128m18:12\u001b[0m  \u001b[38;2;107;113;128m#202-213\u001b[0m  \u001b[38;2;107;113;128mFound it. In `tmux.go:352`: ```go exec.Command(\"tmux\", \"send-keys\", \"-t\", \u001b[0m\u001b[38;2;55;65;81m│\u001b[0m\u001b[48;2;30;41;59m1. **Panic**: `viewport.View()` called with content set but viewport dimensions not properly initialized (width=284, height=78 but content slice capacity=4). This happens in           \u001b[0m\r\n  \u001b[1;38;2;59;130;246mUSER\u001b[0m  \u001b[38;2;107;113;128m18:15\u001b[0m  \u001b[38;2;107;113;128m#214\u001b[0m  \u001b[38;2;107;113;128minput from live works well but from session list `I` act same as before\u001b[0m       \u001b[38;2;55;65;81m│\u001b[0m\u001b[48;2;30;41;59m`openFullConversation` when the viewport content is very short.                                                                                                          "]
[65.170548, "o", "               \u001b[0m\r\n  \u001b[1;38;2;245;158;11mASST\u001b[0m  \u001b[38;2;107;113;128m18:15\u001b[0m  \u001b[38;2;107;113;128m#215-225\u001b[0m  \u001b[38;2;107;113;128mThe session list `I` calls `tmuxPromptAndSend`, not `tmuxSendKeys`. Let me\u001b[0m\u001b[38;2;55;65;81m│\u001b[0m\u001b[48;2;30;41;59m                                                                                                                                                                                        \u001b[0m\r\n  \u001b[1;38;2;59;130;246mUSER\u001b[0m  \u001b[38;2;107;113;128m18:15\u001b[0m  \u001b[38;2;107;113;128m#226\u001b[0m  \u001b[38;2;107;113;128mI think better it uses modal based input not using tmux interface\u001b[0m             \u001b[38;2;55;65;81m│\u001b[0m\u001b[48;2;30;41;59m2. **Agent in message preview**: When selecting an agent sub-item in the conversation list, the preview should be selectable (enter opens agent conversation), which already works.     \u001b[0m\r\n  \u001b[1;38;2;245;158;11mASST\u001b[0m  \u001b[38;2;107;113;128m18:16\u001b[0m  \u001b[38;2;107;113;128m#227-230\u001b[0m  \u001b[38;2;107;113;128mMakes sense — use the same in-app modal input"]
[65.170624, "o", " instead of tmux's command-pr\u001b[0m\u001b[38;2;55;65;81m│\u001b[0m\u001b[48;2;30;41;59mBut you want the agent preview itself to be navigable/selectable — I think you mean the Task block enter in the focused preview should also open agent as conversation view.            \u001b[0m\r\n\n  \u001b[1;38;2;245;158;11mASST\u001b[0m  \u001b[38;2;107;113;128m18:16\u001b[0m  \u001b[38;2;107;113;128m#233-260\u001b[0m  \u001b[38;2;107;113;128mSimple bottom-line prompt, like search. Let me see how it's done for searc\u001b[0m\u001b[38;2;55;65;81m│\u001b[0m\u001b[48;2;30;41;59mLet me fix the panic first, then check the agent preview interaction.                                                                                                                   \u001b[0m\r\n\n  \u001b[1;38;2;245;158;11mASST\u001b[0m  \u001b[38;2;107;113;128m18:18\u001b[0m  \u001b[38;2;107;113;128m#262-283\u001b[0m  \u001b[38;2;107;113;128mNow let me see how the session list passes `filterTerm` to its delegate:\u001b[0m  \u001b[38;2;55;65;81m│\u001b[0m\u001b[38;2;107;113;128m▸\u001b[0m \u001b[1;38;2;16;185;129mTool: Read\u001b[0m  \u001b[38;2;107;113;128m{\"file_path\":\"/Users/gavin.jeong/src/key"]
