[68.45385, "o", "\u001b[0m\u001b[38;2;56;189;248m│\u001b[0m  The panic is in `viewport.View()`. The issue is that when `openFullConversation()` creates a viewport and sets content, the content string might have fewer lines than the viewport   \r\n  \u001b[1;38;2;167;139;250mCMPX\u001b[0m  \u001b[38;2;107;113;128m18:26\u001b[0m  \u001b[38;2;107;113;128m#372\u001b[0m  \u001b[3;38;2;107;113;128mThis session is being continued from a previous conversation that ran out of..\u001b[0m\u001b[38;2;56;189;248m│\u001b[0mheight. But the real problem is that viewport's internal `lines` slice capacity is 4 (very small), yet `visibleLines` tries to slice `[:3791]`. This happens when `SetContent` is       \r\n  \u001b[1;38;2;245;158;11mASST\u001b[0m  \u001b[38;2;107;113;128m18:26\u001b[0m  \u001b[38;2;107;113;128m#373-458\u001b[0m  \u001b[38;2;107;113;128mLet me fix the remaining compilation errors and wire up the tmux config.\u001b[0m  \u001b[38;2;56;189;248m│\u001b[0mcalled before the viewport dimensions are set, or vice versa.                                                                                                                           \r\n"]
