[75.420725, "o", ";107;113;128m18:12\u001b[0m  \u001b[38;2;107;113;128m#201\u001b[0m  \u001b[38;2;107;113;128mabout `I` in session list and its Live modal, send message to the pane make newline after the text it puts, but it should submit it to the claude\u001b[0m                                                                                                                      \r\n  \u001b[1;38;2;245;158;11mASST\u001b[0m  \u001b[38;2;107;113;128m18:12\u001b[0m  \u001b[38;2;107;113;128m#202-213\u001b[0m  \u001b[38;2;107;113;128mFound it. In `tmux.go:352`: ```go exec.Command(\"tmux\", \"send-keys\", \"-t\", target, keys, \"Enter\").Run() ``` The issue is that `tmux send-keys` without `-l` interprets `\"Enter\"` as the Enter key. But the text itself (`keys`) is also being interpreted — special \u001b[0m\r\n  \u001b[1;38;2;59;130;246mUSER\u001b[0m  \u001b[38;2;107;113;128m18:15\u001b[0m  \u001b[38;2;107;113;128m#214\u001b[0m  \u001b[38;2;107;113;128minput from live works well but from session list `I` act same as before\u001b[0m                                                                                                                     "]
