[81.520551, "o", "                                                                                                                                                                                                         \r\n  \u001b[1;38;2;59;130;246mUSER\u001b[0m  \u001b[38;2;107;113;128m18:05\u001b[0m  \u001b[38;2;107;113;128m#111\u001b[0m  \u001b[38;2;107;113;128malso selecable view for agent in message preview? and I got I》bin/ccx Caught panic: runtime error: slice bounds out of range [:3791] with capacity 4 Restoring terminal... goroutine 1 [running]: runtime/debug.Stack() /Users/gavin.jeong/.local/share/mise/instal...\u001b[0m\r\n  \u001b[1;38;2;245;158;11mASST\u001b[0m  \u001b[38;2;107;113;128m18:05\u001b[0m  \u001b[38;2;107;113;128m#112-200\u001b[0m  \u001b[38;2;107;113;128mTwo issues: 1. **Panic**: `viewport.View()` called with content set but viewport dimensions not properly initialized (width=284, height=78 but content slice capacity=4). This happens in `openFullConversation` when the viewport content is very short. 2. **Agen\u001b[0m\r\n  \u001b[1;38;2;59;130;246mUSER\u001b[0m  \u001b[38;2;107;113;128m18:12\u001b[0m  "]
[81.521099, "o", "\u001b[38;2;107;113;128m#201\u001b[0m  \u001b[38;2;107;113;128mabout `I` in session list and its Live modal, send message to the pane make newline after the text it puts, but it should submit it to the claude\u001b[0m                                                                                                                      \r\n  \u001b[1;38;2;245;158;11mASST\u001b[0m  \u001b[38;2;107;113;128m18:12\u001b[0m  \u001b[38;2;107;113;128m#202-213\u001b[0m  \u001b[38;2;107;113;128mFound it. In `tmux.go:352`: ```go exec.Command(\"tmux\", \"send-keys\", \"-t\", target, keys, \"Enter\").Run() ``` The issue is that `tmux send-keys` without `-l` interprets `\"Enter\"` as the Enter key. But the text itself (`keys`) is also being interpreted — special \u001b[0m\r\n  \u001b[1;38;2;59;130;246mUSER\u001b[0m  \u001b[38;2;107;113;128m18:15\u001b[0m  \u001b[38;2;107;113;128m#214\u001b[0m  \u001b[38;2;107;113;128minput from live works well but from session list `I` act same as before\u001b[0m                                                                                                                                             "]
[81.521675, "o", "                                                   \r\n  \u001b[1;38;2;245;158;11mASST\u001b[0m  \u001b[38;2;107;113;128m18:15\u001b[0m  \u001b[38;2;107;113;128m#215-225\u001b[0m  \u001b[38;2;107;113;128mThe session list `I` calls `tmuxPromptAndSend`, not `tmuxSendKeys`. Let me fix that one too:\u001b[0m                                                                                                                                                                       \r\n  \u001b[1;38;2;59;130;246mUSER\u001b[0m  \u001b[38;2;107;113;128m18:15\u001b[0m  \u001b[38;2;107;113;128m#226\u001b[0m  \u001b[38;2;107;113;128mI think better it uses modal based input not using tmux interface\u001b[0m                                                                                                                                                                                                      \r\n  \u001b[1;38;2;245;158;11mASST\u001b[0m  \u001b[38;2;107;113;128m18:16\u001b[0m  \u001b[38;2;107;113;128m#227-230\u001b[0m  \u001b[38;2;107;113;128mMakes sense — use the same in-app modal input instead of tmux's command-prompt. Let me check how "]
